This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it proposes a privacy-preserving attack detection scheme. It also involves the use of encryption techniques to protect sensitive information. 

It is also likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it focuses on attack detection in software-defined networks (SDNs) and involves the analysis of network traffic. 

The cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with the detection of distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attacks, which can affect multiple network domains. 

The cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category is a possibility as the paper deals with distributed attack detection in SDNs. 

Finally, the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category is a possibility as the paper proposes the use of the k-Nearest Neighbors (kNN) algorithm for attack detection and also improves its efficiency.
